# Regulatory Disclosures Insurance Feature Reduces Deductible Indicator

## identifier
de8982

## type
boolean

## definition
Indicate if all insurances have a feature that reduces the deductible to nil when the underlying pool of funds (aggregate deductible) is exhausted.

## guidance
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values
TRUE = when the pool of funds/aggregate deductible becomes nil, the insurer pays the full claim of the member net of any member excess or franchise
FALSE = when the pool of funds/aggregate deductible becomes nil, the insurer does not pay the full claim of the member

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=RegulatoryDisclosures.InsuranceFeatureReducesDeductible.Indicator
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.07
- period=duration
